# Semantic versioning (mealr-api-gateway)

The repo version lives in **`VERSION`** (single line, `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`). Update it **in the same change** whenever you merge meaningful work — do not leave version bumps for a follow-up commit.

## When to bump

| Bump | When | Examples in this repo |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **PATCH** | Backward-compatible fixes; no deploy/config contract change | Docs/README only, Cursor rules, comments, troubleshooting text |
| **MINOR** | Backward-compatible behavior or config **additions** | New `_MAPPINGS` entry + optional/new `cdk-params` key, new stack output, new optional domain behavior |
| **MAJOR** | Breaking changes for operators or downstream consumers | Remove/rename **required** `cdk-params` keys, change `ApiMappingKey` base paths, change default export name, remove a path mapping, require new deploy steps that break existing `cdk-params.json` |

If a change mixes levels, use the **highest** applicable bump.

## Do not bump

- Edits to **`cdk-params.json`** only (gitignored, local).
- WIP or unreleased experiments you are not committing.
- Reverts that restore prior behavior (bump only if the reverted release had already shipped a higher `VERSION` — then bump PATCH to reflect the fix release).

## How to bump

1. Read current version from `VERSION`.
2. Increment per [semver.org](https://semver.org/) rules above.
3. Write the new version as the **only** line in `VERSION` (no `v` prefix, no trailing newline required but one is fine).
4. Include the new version in the **commit message** (e.g. `Add /foo mapping (v0.3.0)` or `Bump version to 0.2.1` for doc-only PATCH).

## Coordination

- If **`README.md`** changes for the same work, follow `.cursor/rules/readme-sync.mdc` as well.
- Do not duplicate version in multiple files — **`VERSION` is the source of truth**.
- When shipping a release, create a GitHub tag **`vX.Y.Z`** with notes per **`.cursor/rules/release-changelog.mdc`** (Keep a Changelog format, compare link, upgrade notes).
